                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d368">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/5796: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-11-26T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 26, 1924—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>295. Your 456, November 25, 5 p.m. You are authorized to associate yourself with
                    the other heads of missions in taking the action outlined in paragraphs 3 and 4
                    making it entirely clear that your action is in no sense to be interpreted as
                    implying a formal recognition.</p>
                <p>The Department concurs in the view generally taken at the meeting of the heads of
                    missions with respect to the provisional character of the present regime and the
                    question of recognition, as reported by you, in paragraph 6.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
